<li id="cite_note-Tilsen-27">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Tilsen_27-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Tilsen_27-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFTilsen">Tilsen, Jon-Jay. <a href="http://www.beki.org/womentefillin.html" class="external text" title="http://www.beki.org/womentefillin.html" rel="nofollow">"Women &amp; Tefillin"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.beki.org/womentefillin.html" class="external free" title="http://www.beki.org/womentefillin.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.beki.org/womentefillin.html</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-08-14</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Women+%26+Tefillin&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Tilsen&amp;rft.aufirst=Jon-Jay&amp;rft.au=Tilsen%2C+Jon-Jay&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.beki.org%2Fwomentefillin.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Tefillin"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-28"><b><a href="#cite_ref-28" title="">^</a></b> Mitzvah 421: ונוהגת מצוה זו בכל זמן, בזכרים אבל לא בנקבות, לפי שהיא מצוה עשה שהזמן גרמא; ומכל-מקום אם רצו להניח אין ממחין בידם ושכר יש להן, אבל לא כשכר האיש, שאינו דומה שכר המצוה ועושה כשכר שאינו מצוה ועושה. ובמסכת ערובין (96-א) בריש פרק המצוה תפלין אמרו זכרונם לברכה שמיכל בת כושי היתה מנחת תפלין ולא מחו בידה חכמים; ושם אמרו: אשתו של יונה היתה עולה לרגל ולא מחו בידה חכמים.<br />
This commandment is in effect for all time, on males but not on females, considering that it is a positive commandment which is entirely time based. Yet in any event, if they want to put on tefilin, they are not to be prevented, and they have a reward -- but it is not like the reward of the man; for there is no resemblance between the reward of a one who is commanded and observes and one who is not commanded and observes. In the Tractate Eruvin (96a) at the beginning of the tenth chapter, the Sages, of blessed memory, said that Michal the daughter of the Chushite would put on tefillin, and the Sages did not protest. They said there too, that the wife of Jonah would ascend [to Jerusalem] for the pillgrimage festivals and the Sages did not prostest.</li>
<li id="cite_note-29"><b><a href="#cite_ref-29" title="">^</a></b> <a href="/wiki/Bo_(parsha)" title="Bo (parsha)">Parashat Bo</a> 16</li>
<li id="cite_note-30"><b><a href="#cite_ref-30" title="">^</a></b> <a href="/wiki/Targum_Pseudo-Jonathan" title="Targum Pseudo-Jonathan">Targum Yerushalmi</a> on <a href="/wiki/Deuteronomy" title="Deuteronomy">Deuteronomy</a> 22:5</li>
<li id="cite_note-31"><b><a href="#cite_ref-31" title="">^</a></b> <a href="/wiki/Shulchan_Aruch" title="Shulchan Aruch">Shulchan Aruch</a> <a href="/wiki/Orach_Chayim" title="Orach Chayim">Orach Chayim</a> 38:3</li>
